  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>dried</strong> <strong>yeast</strong> to a large bowl with 100ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [200ml] </span><strong>warm</strong> <strong>water</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Mix it all together and set aside for 5-10 min for the yeast to develop</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1680013388925-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1680013388925-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1680013388925-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1680013388925-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1680013388925-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong>, a pinch of <strong>sugar </strong>and a crack of <strong>black pepper</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until the tomatoes are starting to blister</p><p>Once blistered, transfer the<strong> cherry tomatoes</strong> to a bowl and reserve the pan</p><p>Add the <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> to the bowl and give everything a good mix up<strong> </strong>– these are your <strong>balsamic tomatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1680013392003-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1680013392003-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1680013392003-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1680013392003-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1680013392003-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>pizza</strong> <strong>base</strong> <strong>mix</strong> to the bowl with the yeast</p><p>Gradually add up to 60ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[120ml] </span><strong>warm</strong> <strong>water</strong> (you may not need all of it), a little at a time, and gently mix with a plastic spatula until a sticky dough ball has formed</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1680013395419-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1680013395419-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1680013395419-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1680013395419-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1680013395419-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Tip the <strong>dough ball</strong> out onto a<strong> floured </strong>work surface and cut into 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span></p><p>Toss each <strong>dough ball</strong> in a light dusting of <strong>flour </strong>until coated, rounding the ball as you go and knead it for 30 secs with floured hands</p><p>Roll out each <strong>dough ball</strong> to approx. 0.5cm thickness with a <strong>floured</strong> <strong>rolling pin </strong>into a circle shape – these are your <strong>pizza bases</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1680013398192-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1680013398192-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1680013398192-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1680013398192-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1680013398192-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Drain the <strong>mozzarella</strong>, then pat and squeeze as much liquid out as you can with kitchen paper</p><p>Tear the <strong>drained mozzarella</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>tomato paste </strong>and <strong>dried basil </strong>to a small bowl with the <strong>truffle oil </strong>and 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> – this is your<strong> truffle & tomato sauce</strong></p><p>Spread the <strong>truffle & tomato sauce</strong> over only half of each <strong>pizza base</strong>, then top with the<strong> torn mozzarella</strong> and the <strong>sliced prosciutto</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1680013401118-x200.jpg",
